OL,3,CWomen in Guernsey call for more
OL,4,Csupport and awareness for dyslexia
OL,6,FShe says the issue was the lack of
OL,7,Fawareness in school: "At the time it
OL,8,Fwasn't something we spoke about, there
OL,9,Fwasn't big awareness around it which
OL,10,Fdidn't help.
OL,12,F"Now I would hope schools would pick
OL,13,Fup on these things a little bit
OL,14,Fquicker and our children today
OL,15,Fwouldn't have to struggle through
OL,16,Fschool life and then question
OL,17,Fthemselves as an adult."
OL,19,FAround 10 to 15% of people in the
OL,20,FChannel Islands are thought to have
OL,21,Fdyslexia.
