OL,3,CWomen in Guernsey call for more
OL,4,Csupport and awareness for dyslexia
OL,6,FHilary Greening, a dyslexia specialist
OL,7,Fsays the condition can affect people
OL,8,Fin more than one way: "If you ask most
OL,9,Fpeople what dyslexia means to them
OL,10,Fthey talk about jumbling letters, not
OL,11,Fbeing good at spelling or maybe you'll
OL,12,Fgrow out of it, but it is much more
OL,13,Fthan that.
OL,15,F"It affects people's lives and Vicki
OL,16,Fwas an example of that, it affects
OL,17,Fconcentration, memory, coordination,
OL,18,Fmental calculations, mathematics."
