OL,3,CWomen in Guernsey call for more
OL,4,Csupport and awareness for dyslexia
OL,6,FHer workplace is learning to embrace
OL,7,Fneurodiversity through online training
OL,8,Fto change perceptions about
OL,9,Fdifferences such as dyslexia.
OL,11,FHilary says the training is important
OL,12,Ffor the future of workplaces, "the
OL,13,Fmain thing about that is to raise
OL,14,Fawareness and to advocate, and the way
OL,15,Fwe need to do that is through training.
OL,17,FShe added, "That is the key to
OL,18,Fupskilling people within schools and
OL,19,Fthe workplace so they have a better
OL,20,Funderstanding of the potential they
OL,21,Fare missing out on."
